do you like my new poem lords and ladies of the court i present to you this day a story of great tenderness about a lamb who d gone astray youngest son of the earl of boeing a child who didn t like the crust with his torn shirt and scraped knees aspire to great things he must the mountainous climb before him surveyed from a comfortable chair and the list of sad sacrifices was more than the boy could bear musical notes and algebra quotes shakespearian exaltation plato and plutarch calvin and kant and rousseau s grand explanation diamonds and fields were his geometry round balls and ones that wobble cleats sticks polls and flags played on the sand mud and the cobble older and bolder the youngest son grew with a world out there to explore lashed out at those who protected him and left with a slam of the door with powerful legs and shoulders so broad they could support the largest of chips a sarcastic grin and smackable chin a quick mind and cold callous lips angry source of comedic bile confident clown of the seas had a laugh at all s expense until an unhappy god he displeased left adrift without water abandoned on unfriendly shores alone for a day a month then a year left to pray to his own faceless lord now old and gray at his terminal he can laugh at the fool that he was collecting affection with nickels and dimes and thanking the great god above this one intrigues me is god great or is he faceless to our armchair mountaineer apparently now he's great in a small change loose change sort of way the bigger the shoulder the bigger the chip love it displeasing an unhappy god so much easier to do that pissing off a jolly buddha wow quite a saga Shaggy dog story Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an John the Baptist William Shakespeare One Piece minor characters Equine conformation The Amber Spyglass Piccolo Junior Saga Moon Aphrodite Shawn Michaels Shark Professional wrestling throws AFI 100 Years series David Bowie Knife Moloch Conan the Barbarian Deluge (mythol